  "summary": {
    "as": "Introduced", 
    "date": "1999-07-30", 
    "text": "Safe Sunscreen, Healthy Skin Act - Directs the Commissioner of Food and Drugs to require over the counter drug sunscreen products which are designed to screen the ultra violet rays of the sun to include on the label a date beyond which the product is not effective and recommendations for product storage to avoid reducing product effectiveness. Provides that such a product which does not contain the date and storage recommendations shall be considered to be a misbranded drug for purposes of the Federal Food, Drug, and Cosmetic Act."
  }, 
